Key Match Events: Kiké Hernández's home run provided half of the runs in Game 5.
Yoshinobu Yamamoto pitched five scoreless innings in Game 5.
The Dodgers' bullpen had a 2.10 ERA and 27 strikeouts in 25⅔ innings during the series.
Dodgers pitchers put up consecutive shutouts in the postseason for just the third time in franchise history.
Fernando Tatis Jr. hit into a double play in the third inning of Game 5, extinguishing the final threat from the Padres.
Teoscar Hernández hit a seventh-inning home run in Game 5.
Post-Match Reflections: Kiké Hernández commented on the strength of the Padres team after the series win.
Andrew Friedman praised the Dodgers' bullpen for their execution.
Dave Roberts likened the series' intensity to the Dodgers' 2020 NLCS against the Braves and the 2004 Red Sox against the Yankees.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Dodgers' record in elimination games under Dave Roberts improved to 13-7.
Shohei Ohtani struggled against Yu Darvish, going 0-for-6 with three strikeouts in the NLDS.
